ЁЯЪА Day 90/100 #100DaysOfCode Challenge Update!

ЁЯФМ Deep Dive into Networking: Fiber Optic vs. Copper Cables

Excited to share my learnings from Day 90 of my #100DaysOfCode journey! Today, I explored the fascinating world of network cablesтАФunderstanding their types, standards, and best practices.
Key Takeaways:

тЬФ Fiber Optic Cables тЖТ Use light for data transmission (Single Mode vs. Multimode).
тЬФ Copper Cables (Ethernet) тЖТ Cat5e, Cat6, Cat6a тАУ each with different speeds & use cases.
тЬФ Common Issues тЖТ Crosstalk (NEXT/FEXT), Attenuation, and termination errors.
тЬФ Standards Matter! тЖТ TIA defines cable categories, while IEEE sets Ethernet standards.
Whether you're setting up a home network or managing enterprise infrastructure, choosing the right cable is crucial!

